ferc_filing_data.tariff_title: Meyersdale Storage, LLC Reactive Power Rate Schedule

record_data.record_plain_text: MEYERSDALE STORAGE, LLC REACTIVE RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1 Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service Meyersdale Storage, LLC (Meyersdale Storage) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service (Reactive Supply Service) from the Meyersdale Battery Storage Project (Storage Project). The Storage Project is an 18 MW lithium-ion battery storage facility located in Somerset County, Pennsylvania. The Storage Project is interconnected to the Mid-Atlantic Interstate Transmission LLC's 115 kV Meyersdale North substation in the Penelec transmission zone and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (PJM). This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Meyersdale Storage's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Storage Project. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Meyersdale Storage's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Meyersdale Storage shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff. MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $837,437 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $69,786.42
